    <fr:title text="Sections of sections are unique › "><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002Q.xml" title="Sections of sections are unique" addr="forest://erct/erct-002Q" type="local"><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">Sections</fr:link> of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> are unique</fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Using the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0015.xml" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions" addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" type="local">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</fr:link>, we can see that the type of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0025.xml" title="Retract" addr="forest://erct/erct-0025" type="local">retract</fr:link> of the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  -]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{B}]]></fr:tex>, using the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0023.xml" title="Path object structure on sections" addr="forest://erct/erct-0023" type="local">univalence principle for sections</fr:link>.</html:p>

 <html:p>To show that the type of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> already, we know that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000U.xml" title="Biinverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000U" type="local">biinvertible</fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002N.xml" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible" addr="forest://erct/erct-002N" type="local">therefore</fr:link> that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">contractible</fr:link>. By <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0026.xml" title="Propositions are closed under retracts" addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" /></fr:link>, it suffices to show that the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  -]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{B}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>, which follows via <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001K.xml" title="Contractible types are propositions" addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002O.xml" title="Pushforward along biinvertible maps" addr="forest://erct/erct-002O" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002O" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
